HEADWORD: Whereto
<hw>Where*to"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To which; -- used relatively.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Whereto</xex> we have already attained.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Phil.
iii. 16.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Whereto</qex> all bonds do tie me day by day.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To what; to what end; -- used
interrogatively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whereunto</ent>⟦br⟧
